# Loomis — Roles and Scope

## Role → Tenant Scope
| Role | `tenant_id` in JWT | Notes |
|------|-------------------|-------|
| `platform_owner` | null | Global access |
| `platform_admin` | null | Global; break-glass requires ticket |
| `dpo` | null | Compliance functions only |
| `regional_manager` | null | Read across assigned region; onboard schools |
| `regional_subordinate` | null | Read own portfolio; onboard schools |
| `school_owner` | tenant UUID | Highest school-level role |
| `principal` | tenant UUID | School operations |
| `admin_officer` | tenant UUID | Admissions, student registry, staff onboarding |
| `accountant` | tenant UUID | Fee config, payment verification |
| `cashier` | tenant UUID | Log payments only; cannot verify |
| `exam_officer` | tenant UUID | Exams, grading schemes, result publish |
| `deputy_exam_officer` | tenant UUID | Activated only after 72h Exam Officer inactivity |
| `timetable_officer` | tenant UUID | Timetable builder |
| `teacher` | tenant UUID | Gradebook for own subjects; no attendance |
| `class_teacher` | tenant UUID | Attendance for own class + Teacher capabilities |
| `parent` | null | Cross-tenant; scoped to linked children only |
| `student` | tenant UUID | Own data only |

## Hard Rules (enforce in middleware AND service layer)
- **Class Teacher only** marks attendance. Teachers have zero access to attendance endpoints.
- **Teacher** enters grades for own assigned subjects only. Class Teachers have READ-ONLY gradebook access.
- **Cashier** who logs a payment CANNOT verify it. Check `payment.logged_by_id !== req.user.id` in the verify handler.
- **Regional Manager** CANNOT approve their own subordinate's KYC. Check `kyc.subject_user_id not in manager's subordinates`.
- **Deputy Exam Officer** is only active when `exam_officer.last_active_at < now() - 72h`. Check this at the service layer on every Deputy action.
- **Parent** dashboard queries are SEPARATE per-tenant DB round-trips. Never JOIN across tenants for parent data.
- **Platform Admin** can only access tenant data via a break-glass session (requires support ticket ID).

## `requireRole` Usage
```typescript
// Single role
app.post('/attendance', { preHandler: [authenticate, requireRole('class_teacher')] }, handler);

// Multiple allowed roles
app.post('/admissions', { preHandler: [authenticate, requireRole('admin_officer', 'principal')] }, handler);

// Platform-only routes
app.get('/admin/tenants', { preHandler: [authenticate, requireRole('platform_admin', 'platform_owner')] }, handler);
```
